<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Seated-Wide-Grip-Cable-Row">Seated Wide Grip Cable Row</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/seated-wide-grip-cable-row" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">seated wide grip cable row</a> is another effective upper-body workout guaranteed to help sculpt and define your back muscles. The cable machine provides constant tension which increases the overall training volume leading to <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8884877/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">greater muscle gains</a>. It primarily targets the shoulder and back muscles with secondary activation of the biceps.</p>



<p>The grip is important during this exercise to maximize target muscle activation. Studies found that, while using a neutral grip, the trapezius muscles can achieve maximum muscle activation rates of <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/371114847_Effect_Of_Different_Grip_Position_And_Shoulder-_Abduction_Angle_On_Muscle_Strength_And_Activation_During_The_Seated_Cable_Row" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">116%–138%</a>. This demonstrates the effectiveness of this exercise on middle-back muscle engagement.&nbsp;</p>



<p>This exercise would be a great addition to a <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/back-and-shoulder-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">back and shoulders workout</a>, upper-body lift, or a functional strength routine.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Seated Wide-Grip Cable Row" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1002659684?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Seated Wide-Grip Cable Row Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Attach a wide bar to the low pulley on the cable machine. Load with appropriate weight for your fitness level and goals.</li>



<li>Sit on the bench with your feet on the foot supports. Grasp the bar at the widest grip outside the bend of the bar.</li>



<li>Sit up straight, inhale, and engage your core.</li>



<li>Exhale, and slowly pull the bar towards your midline. Focus on squeezing the shoulder blades together.</li>



<li>Pull back as far as you can, fully flexing your elbows. Hold for one count at the end position for maximum activation.</li>



<li>Inhale, and gradually release the bar forward, back to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of reps and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Maintain control throughout, being careful not to drop the weight at any point.</li>



<li>Keep your core and back engaged to avoid straining the lower back leading to injury.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Focus on pulling back with your elbows and concentrating on squeezing the shoulder blades together. This will improve the <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26700744/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">mind-muscle connection</a> for optimal results.</li>
</ul>



